# Infrastructure Layer Rules

## Purpose

Implement domain interfaces with concrete technologies (Dexie, Ollama, Chrome APIs, DOM).

## Structure

```
src/infrastructure/
├── storage/
│   ├── dexie-storage.ts
│   ├── dexie-lead-repository.ts
│   └── mappers/              # DB row ↔ Domain entity
├── whatsapp/
│   ├── dom-whatsapp-adapter.ts
│   ├── store-whatsapp-adapter.ts
│   └── whatsapp-adapter-factory.ts
├── llm/
│   ├── ollama-provider.ts
│   ├── web-llm-provider.ts
│   └── cloud-api-provider.ts
├── messaging/
│   └── chrome-message-bus.ts
└── agents/
    ├── reply-triage-agent.ts
    └── lead-scoring-agent.ts
```

## Adapter Pattern (MANDATORY)

Every external system gets an adapter implementing a domain interface:

```typescript
// Domain defines contract
interface IWhatsAppAdapter extends IMessageSender, IMessageReader, IContactReader {}

// Infrastructure implements
export class DomWhatsAppAdapter implements IWhatsAppAdapter {
  async send(chatId: string, text: string): Promise<SendResult> {
    // DOM manipulation here — NEVER in domain/application
  }
}
```

## Mapper Pattern

Convert between infrastructure types and domain entities in dedicated mapper files:

```typescript
// src/infrastructure/storage/mappers/lead.mapper.ts
export function toDomain(row: LeadRow): Lead { ... }
export function toRow(lead: Lead): LeadRow { ... }
```

Mappers are pure functions. No side effects.

## Zod Validation at Boundaries

Validate ALL external data before mapping to domain:

```typescript
const OllamaResponseSchema = z.object({
  response: z.string(),
  done: z.boolean(),
});

const parsed = OllamaResponseSchema.safeParse(rawJson);
if (!parsed.success) throw new InfrastructureError('Invalid LLM response');
```

## Chrome API Usage

- All `chrome.*` calls live ONLY in infrastructure or entrypoints
- Wrap chrome APIs in small utility classes (e.g., `ChromeAlarmScheduler`, `ChromeNotifier`)
- Handle service worker lifecycle: persist state, re-register alarms on startup

## LLM Provider Implementation

```typescript
export class OllamaProvider implements ILLMProvider {
  constructor(private readonly baseUrl: string) {}

  async *generate(request: LLMRequest): AsyncIterable<string> {
    const response = await fetch(`${this.baseUrl}/api/generate`, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ model: request.model, prompt: request.prompt, stream: true }),
    });
    // Parse and yield chunks with Zod validation
  }
}
```

## WhatsApp Safety in Adapters

- `send()` must include configurable delay before actual send
- Check connection state before send; return `SendResult` with error, don't throw
- Rate limit tracking in adapter (messages sent in last hour/day)

## Error Handling

- Use `InfrastructureError` for external system failures
- Include retry metadata where applicable
- Never let raw fetch/chrome errors propagate to application layer

## Testing

- Use fake/in-memory implementations for unit tests
- Integration tests with real Dexie (fake-indexeddb)
- Mock fetch for LLM provider tests
